{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bbb7d1fb-7a02-4446-91b9-cc5780053f28","content":"\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is absent.\n\n2. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable (`MyTests.exe`).\n\n3. **Watch for breaking changes:**\n   - CLI args differ — e.g. `--filter` becomes `--filter` but syntax may vary; use `--help` on the test binary.\n   - `.runsettings` are still supported, but some VSTest-specific adapter settings may not apply.\n   - If you use `dotnet test`, ensure your SDK is recent enough (≥ .NET SDK 8.0.4xx or 9+) for full integration.\n\nThat's it — the SDK handles the rest (entry point, references, etc.). No additional NuGet packages are needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"821f1d1c-2b12-4211-aa70-9e4503755784","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in a specific repo.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":374},"id":"3c89530c-e9ff-4397-898c-6a9339e6abd3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:45:36.848Z","parentId":"6d3b6c06-12d7-484c-a10d-0604138c1657"}
